      "writtenOn": "2017-11-02T17:58:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In luci, for tasks like these, we usually just write a normal function and use parallel.FanOutIn() to wrap it.\nhttps://cs.chromium.org/chromium/infra/go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/common/sync/parallel/workPool.go?q\u003dfanoutin\u0026sq\u003dpackage:chromium\u0026dr\u003dCSs\u0026l\u003d44\n\n\nSo make this into getOncallData(c, url) (resp.Oncall, error) { ... }\n\nAnd use FanOutIn(gen func(chan\u003c- func() error)) error\n\nOne more thing is to add a memcache layer here, with like a ~15min expiration.",
